  "narrative": {
    "intro": "This ranking summarizes contractor obligations for FY2026 to date, with total obligations of $191B. The list highlights the top contractors by obligations and shows a mix of construction, healthcare, defense, and services firms. FISHER SAND & GRAVEL CO leads the list with $13.3B in obligations, followed by TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $12.6B and two entries for LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $10B and $8.8B. Other notable contractors include MCKESSON CORPORATION at $9.9B, ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION at $8.3B, and OPTUM PUBLIC SECTOR SOLUTIONS, INC. at $6.6B. The ranking also lists BARNARD CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, INCORPORATED at $5.9B, THE BOEING COMPANY at $5.8B, and TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC at $5.1B. Total award value figures shown are full contract values, not single-year obligations, so reported amounts reflect contract value rather than only the portion obligated within a single fiscal year.",
    "sections": [
